## Problem Statement

You have no single place to start your day with orientation. Daily briefing, financial pulse, active projects, and a dose of motivation are scattered across apps, files, and conversation threads. The result is a slow, unfocused start requiring manual context-gathering before real work begins. A persistent, live Cowork dashboard fixes this by pulling everything into one place that opens ready to go.

---

## Goals

1. Reduce time-to-oriented in the morning from 10+ minutes to under 60 seconds.
2. Surface the daily briefing automatically so you never miss a scheduled summary.
3. Provide a financial snapshot (investments + budget) without opening a separate app.
4. Keep active projects visible so context-switching starts with a reminder, not a search.
5. Deliver a daily motivational anchor that sets tone for the session.

---

## Non-Goals

- **Not a full financial dashboard.** No transaction history, charts, or portfolio analytics — just a snapshot. Deep finance work stays in dedicated tools.
- **Not a task manager.** TASKS.md and the productivity plugin own task tracking. This dashboard reads from that system, it does not replace it.
- **Not a notification center.** No inbox, Slack, or alerts. This is a pull surface, not push.
- **Not mobile-optimized for v1.** Desktop Cowork is the only target. Mobile layout is a v2 concern.
- **Not multi-user.** This is a personal tool for a single user — no sharing, collaboration, or permissions.

---

## User Stories

### Morning Orientation

As a user, I want to open Mission Control each morning and immediately see what is scheduled for the day so that I can orient myself without digging through calendar apps or conversation history.

As a user, I want my daily briefing (auto-generated by a scheduled Cowork task) to appear on the dashboard so that I can read it in one place rather than hunting through past sessions.

### Financial Awareness

As a user, I want a quick snapshot of my current investment balances and budget status so that I can stay financially aware without breaking my work flow to open a separate app.

As a user, I want the financial widget to show whether I am on track with my budget for the month so that I catch drift early rather than at month-end.

### Project Context

As a user, I want to see my active projects listed with their current status so that I can pick up exactly where I left off without re-reading project files.

As a user, I want each project card to link directly to its project page in my knowledge base so that one click gets me into context.

### Motivation

As a user, I want a motivational or philosophical quote to appear each day so that sessions start with intention rather than just a to-do list.

