## Requirements

### Must-Have (P0)

**Daily Briefing Widget**
- Displays the most recent scheduled briefing output from the Cowork scheduled task system.
- Shows briefing date and timestamp.
- If no briefing has run today, shows the most recent one with a staleness label.
- Acceptance criteria: briefing text is readable, timestamped, and refreshes when the page reloads.

**Active Projects Widget**
- Lists all projects with status "active" from [enter path to your projects folder here].
- Displays project name and status badge.
- Each entry links to the corresponding project page.
- Acceptance criteria: list reflects the current state of the projects folder on page load; clicking a project opens the correct file or page.

**Motivational Quote Widget**
- Displays one quote per day, rotating daily.
- Quote source can be a hardcoded curated list for v1.
- Acceptance criteria: a quote is always visible; it does not change mid-session (only on new day).

**Investment / Budget Snapshot Widget**
- Shows current investment total and monthly budget status (on track / over / under).
- Data source for v1: a JSON or markdown file you maintain at [enter path to your financial data file here] that Claude reads.
- Acceptance criteria: widget renders the values from the source file; if the file is missing or malformed, shows a clear "data unavailable" state.

**Persistent Cowork Artifact**
- Dashboard is built as a Cowork artifact so it persists across sessions.
- Refreshes data on page load.
- Acceptance criteria: artifact opens without requiring a new conversation; data is current as of last page load.

---

### Nice-to-Have (P1)

**Quick Stats Bar**
- One-line summary at the top: number of active projects, days until next scheduled event, budget % used.
- Gives you an at-a-glance number before reading any widget.

**Briefing History Drawer**
- Expandable panel to view the last 7 briefings.
- Useful for catching up after time away.

**Quote Source Expansion**
- Pull quotes from a dedicated quotes file at [enter path to your quotes file here] so you can curate the pool yourself.

**Project Status Inline Edit**
- Ability to change a project status (active / paused / shipped) directly from the dashboard without opening the project file.

---

### Future Considerations (P2)

**Live Investment Data**
- Connect to a financial API or brokerage MCP to pull real-time balances instead of a manually maintained file.

**Calendar Integration**
- Pull today's events from Google Calendar via the Calendar MCP and display them in the briefing widget.

**Mobile Layout**
- Responsive design for Cowork on mobile.

**Multi-Widget Customization**
- Drag-and-drop widget layout; show/hide individual widgets.

